				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Roth wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I have 12 different tiles that will need to be updated upon a button press (this is in NMI, as was recommended to me earlier in IRC), so it would be really bad to do that 12 times. I cannot figure out a good way to do it though :/  If anyone can give me some direction, or some addressing modes to look into, I'd appreciate it.</div><br />To make it as fast as possible, you'd really have to repeat the code 12 times. But I don't think this is necessary, since 12 tiles is not that much, and you should be fine with a loop. Just break you address table into 2, one for the high bytes and one for the lower ones, so that you can access all the information with the same index. Or get rid of the high bytes, if they're all $20 like you said. The loop would look something like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;ldx #11<br />copy_tiles:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda filltopleftHi, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2006<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda filltopleftLo, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2006<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;lda x_tiles, x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sta $2007<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;dex<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bpl copy_tiles</div><br /><br />By looking at you address table, I can see that the ones in the same row are consecutive addresses, so you could very well benefit from the auto-incrementing nature of the PPU address, and only set the address through $2006 once once for every 4 bytes written to $2007, saving you a lot of VBlank cycles. If you however want to use this code when the addresses are not consecutive, then this doesn't apply.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">My second snag is the original nametable itself. After manipulating it as above, the whole nametable seems to shift down a couple/few pixels. I found <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=4776#4776" class="postlink">a post by Disch</a> that says to write to the scroll after doing the updates, which helped to stop the entire original nametable from shifting WAY off from the original placement, but it still shifts a tad now. I'm not sure how to keep it stable.</div>
<br />There is no reason for the position of the name table to be unstable if you correctly set the scroll (through $2000 and $2005) every frame during the VBlank period after you're done using $2006 and $2007. Just respect those rules and you'll be safe. Are you sure you're respecting those rules? Are you sure your NMI code isn't taking to long and going past VBlank time?</div>

