				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">bunnyboy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The 2006 may be redundant, but is there a better order for the rest?</div>
<br />EDIT: Didn't notice you asked about the order...
<br />
<br />Well, in my game (which scrolls around a lot), I first write to $2005 and then to $2000, and it works just fine. But I really don't think the order matters at all. The bits that are used for scrolling are only copied to the address register when the frame starts anyway, so as long as you do it before the frame starts, the order shouldn't matter.
<br />
<br />I don't see the need to write to $2001 every frame, because it doesn't have parameters altered by other PPU operations, like using $2006/$2007 affects the scroll. There is also no need to disable rendering during VBlank, it's safe to use $2006 and $2007 with rendering enabled if you do it during VBlank time. Because of this it's possible to get away with not writing to $2001 every frame. Unless you constantly change grayscale or color emphasis bits, but that's usually not the case. There is no side effect to writing to $2001 though, so you're free to do as you wish.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

